# godot-usd-bridge
# Distilled from the standard GitHub C++ / CMake / VisualStudio and Godot 4
# templates, trimmed to what this project actually produces.

# ── CMake build output (presets build out-of-source) ──
/build/
/out/
cmake-build-*/

# ── OpenUSD: cloned, built, and installed locally by scripts/build_usd.ps1 ──
/thirdparty/

# ── Compiled artifacts (binaries ship via release zips, never committed) ──
*.dll
*.pdb
*.exp
*.ilk
*.obj
*.lib
*.so
*.dylib

# ── Addon: only the .gdextension manifest and license texts are committed; ──
# ── the binaries (above) and USD plugin resources (below) are build output ──
/addons/godot-usd-bridge/usd/

# ── Godot editor cache / import DB for the demo project (regenerated) ──
.godot/

# ── Demo project's local copy of the addon (CMake installs it here from the ──
# ── repo-root addons/ dir so `godot --path demo` can load it; not committed) ──
/demo/addons/

# ── Visual Studio / MSVC ──
.vs/
*.user

# ── Editors & OS ──
.vscode/
.idea/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db